description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for an appropriately skilled and experienced speech and language therapist to lead our Head &amp; Neck service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be based at the Royal Devon &amp; Exeter Hospital (RD&amp;E) and work closely with multidisciplinary and SLT colleagues to ensure the highest standards of patient-centred care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The RD&amp;E provides a full range of ENT services to the population of Exeter, Mid and East Devon. It is a designated cancer centre and part of the Peninsula Cancer Network. The successful applicant will work within a dedicated multidisciplinary setting and in liaison with team members from Torbay, Taunton and North Devon District Hospitals.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are a strong, cohesive adult SLT service spanning acute, community and learning disabilities, with excellent systems in place for supervision, support and continuing professional development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a permanent, part time position of 30 hours per week (0.8 wte). For more information, please contact Marianne Bos-Clark, Lead SLT for ENT, on 01392 402489 or mbos-clark@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our vision is to provide safe, high quality seamless services delivered with courtesy and respect. To achieve our vision we expect all our staff to uphold our Trust values. Our Trust values are: &lt;br /&gt; Honesty, Openness &amp; Integrity&lt;br /&gt; Fairness&lt;br /&gt; Inclusion &amp; Collaboration&lt;br /&gt; Respect &amp; Dignity&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;***Preference will be given to staff with ‘Priority’ and &#39;At Risk&#39; status including NHS At Risk staff throughout Devon.***&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;DUE TO THE ANTICIPATED HIGH NUMBER OF APPLICATIONS FOR THIS POST WE RESERVE THE RIGHT TO CLOSE THE VACANCY BEFORE THE CLOSING DATE.&lt;/p&gt;
